<i>But I will fear no evil</i>

02:53.569 --> 02:55.705
Oh, my God.

02:55.905 --> 02:57.040
Mom?

02:57.240 --> 02:59.843
Wait, Brady.

03:00.043 --> 03:02.261
Brady, honey, honey, no.

03:02.461 --> 03:04.680
GGo... Go to bed, honey.

03:04.880 --> 03:07.717
Go to bed, okay?

03:07.917 --> 03:08.718
Stop it.

03:08.918 --> 03:11.254
It's big people time, okay?

03:11.454 --> 03:12.522
Okay, honey?

03:12.722 --> 03:13.589
Beat it, you little shit.

03:16.426 --> 03:18.761
Good boy, go... go... go to bed.

03:18.961 --> 03:21.998
MomMommy's having private time,
good boy.

03:22.198 --> 03:25.401
Okay.

03:32.275 --> 03:35.545
Oh!

03:39.949 --> 03:42.251
Oh, my god.

03:42.451 --> 03:44.754
Oh, God. Oh!

03:54.831 --> 03:57.600
And good morning, Ohio. I'm John Moore.

03:57.800 --> 03:58.601
And I'm Amanda Collins.

03:58.801 --> 04:00.036
We have a lot coming up for you,

04:00.236 --> 04:02.205
the latest on the big trial
we've been following,

04:02.405 --> 04:03.573
obviously, some traffic this morning

04:03.773 --> 04:05.308
you need to know about,
and your weather.

04:05.508 --> 04:07.026
But, first, going to a segment.

04:07.226 --> 04:08.544
We're going to talk about your dog

04:08.744 --> 04:11.714
and how obedient that dog
is around the house.

04:11.914 --> 04:13.650
I got this problem with...

04:13.850 --> 04:15.818
Maybe the problem is more with
my wife than with the dog.

04:16.017 --> 04:18.553
But the dog, this big German Shepherd,

04:18.754 --> 04:20.189
kind of thinks the place is his,

04:20.389 --> 04:21.390
and he is on that couch...

04:21.589 --> 04:22.659
Hey, come sit.

04:22.859 --> 04:24.077
every time my wife leaves the room.

04:24.277 --> 04:25.295
I feel like he's looking...
I'm fine.

04:25.495 --> 04:27.063
over at me, "Hey,
she doesn't know we're here."

04:27.263 --> 04:28.331
It's not healthy to eat standing up.

04:28.531 --> 04:30.733
As soon as she comes back in,
"Why'd you let him get there?"

04:30.933 --> 04:32.301
But he's always happy to see me.

04:32.501 --> 04:33.670
I come home. The tail is wagging.

04:33.870 --> 04:36.839
He doesn't care how long I've been gone,
where I've been.

04:37.039 --> 04:39.742
So you're saying your wife
isn't happy to see you?

04:39.942 --> 04:45.248
SShe likes me maybe three days
a week when it's payday.

04:46.382 --> 04:48.117
All that aside, it's a bit serious.

04:48.317 --> 04:51.320
"Traing your Dog" segment...
if you have a problem dog,

04:51.520 --> 04:53.456
stick around. You'll want to learn...

04:56.092 --> 04:58.427
And sometimes it works
and sometimes it doesn't.

05:07.403 --> 05:11.741
I've got a pocket full of money

05:11.941 --> 05:14.110
And a heart full of love

05:18.414 --> 05:22.351
I got a pocket full of money, whoo, yes

05:22.551 --> 05:25.021
And a heart full of love

05:28.357 --> 05:31.777
Well, let's cuddle up

05:31.977 --> 05:35.398
And act like a turtledove

05:40.002 --> 05:44.540
Now, I've got a few things
that I want you to do

05:44.740 --> 05:46.943
I just ain't had time, darling...

06:03.626 --> 06:06.028
Check this out.

06:14.003 --> 06:15.705
Holy shit.

06:17.840 --> 06:20.543
Can we get a tarp on this
before it washes away?

06:20.743 --> 06:22.511
Already on its way.

06:34.857 --> 06:37.860
It's registered
to a Mrs. Olivia Trelawney,

06:38.060 --> 06:40.396
1127 Ashley Way, Apartment 19C.

06:40.596 --> 06:41.730
It's in Sugar Heights.

06:41.930 --> 06:43.065
Got a phone number?

06:43.265 --> 06:44.233
I can get one.

06:44.433 --> 06:45.668
Yeah!

06:50.806 --> 06:51.540
No airbag deployment.

06:54.010 --> 06:55.545
He disabled them.

06:55.745 --> 06:57.747
Speaks to premeditation.

06:57.947 --> 07:00.216
Speaks to him knowing how to do it.

07:00.416 --> 07:02.184
You get a whiff?

07:02.384 --> 07:03.519
Ohh!

07:03.719 --> 07:06.505
He must have used
3, 4 gallons of bleach.

07:06.705 --> 07:09.492
This'll be a forensics
fucking deelight.

07:11.994 --> 07:16.448
Well, let's get together

07:16.648 --> 07:21.103
And hug up like a turtledove

07:44.860 --> 07:46.195
Nice.

07:47.863 --> 07:50.433
Yeah.
I'm laying in a hospital bed halfdead.

07:50.633 --> 07:51.467
You two can't be bothered.

07:54.103 --> 07:56.605
Did you take a frigging beat to worry,

07:56.805 --> 07:58.607
show some concern?

07:58.807 --> 08:00.543
I'm sorry.

08:00.743 --> 08:03.145
I'm in oral motor rehabilitation.

08:03.345 --> 08:04.547
I sustained nerve damage.

08:04.747 --> 08:07.049
I got to suck on this 4 hours a day.

08:07.249 --> 08:07.950
DDid they visit?

08:10.753 --> 08:12.121
They're parttimers.

08:12.321 --> 08:14.473
Yeah. Well, us fulltimers thought

08:14.673 --> 08:16.826
that you'd want us to mind the store.

08:23.232 --> 08:24.700
Did you fuck with my computer?

08:26.168 --> 08:27.403
What?

08:27.603 --> 08:28.988
One second, it's working perfect.

08:29.188 --> 08:30.573
The next, it nearly killed me.

08:30.773 --> 08:32.308
That is messed up, Robi.

08:32.508 --> 08:35.277
Seriously, that's almost cruel.

08:36.611 --> 08:38.179
What kind of monster do you think I am?

08:46.188 --> 08:48.090
Sorry. Sorry.

08:48.290 --> 08:52.862
I pride myself on being on time,
which I never am.

08:55.364 --> 08:57.166
Somebody dead?

08:57.366 --> 08:58.034
Sorry?

08:58.234 --> 09:00.336
I see retired people in ties,

09:00.536 --> 09:04.006
my brain immediately goes to funerals.

09:04.206 --> 09:07.676
Well, the tie just means I'm on the job.

09:08.878 --> 09:10.012
Our job.

09:10.212 --> 09:11.147
Yeah.

09:11.347 --> 09:12.548
You want to sit down?

09:12.748 --> 09:15.451
I did go to the storage space.

09:15.651 --> 09:18.354
Turns out he wrote her a letter,

09:18.554 --> 09:21.057
more than one, in fact.

09:21.257 --> 09:22.491
This good?
Yes.

09:30.065 --> 09:34.069
Anybody who intentionally
mows down innocent people

09:34.269 --> 09:35.838
is a sick fuck,

09:36.038 --> 09:38.541
but...

09:38.741 --> 09:40.109
this guy is so much worse.

09:59.228 --> 10:00.463
"Dear Olivia Trelawney..."

10:01.997 --> 10:03.866
"I am the man who stole your Mercedes.

10:04.066 --> 10:05.268
To the public, I am a monster,

10:05.468 --> 10:09.205
but I want you to know
that I am also a human being."

10:09.405 --> 10:11.040
Really? Okay.

10:11.240 --> 10:14.877
I grew up in a physically
and sexually abusive household.

10:15.077 --> 10:18.080
I was bullied at school, laughed at,

10:18.280 --> 10:22.084
and not just by the other kids,
but by teachers, too.

10:22.284 --> 10:24.586
I was never a mean kid, Mrs. Trelawney.

10:24.786 --> 10:26.972
I just tried to get through my childhood

10:27.172 --> 10:29.358
without being laughed at or humiliated.

10:29.558 --> 10:31.861
I did not succeed.

10:32.061 --> 10:33.462
I work in a lowpaying job

10:33.662 --> 10:35.831
and lead what most people
would consider to be

10:36.031 --> 10:38.634
a bad and unremarkable life.

10:38.834 --> 10:41.237
Finally, I began to get angry.

10:41.437 --> 10:43.739
I wanted to strike back at the world

10:43.939 --> 10:46.042
and make the world know I was alive.

10:46.242 --> 10:48.944
"One day, it all got to be too much.
I didn't plan ahead.

10:49.144 --> 10:50.913
I just couldn't take it anymore,
and I..."

10:51.113 --> 10:53.382
This is bullshit.
He thought ahead, planned it.

10:53.582 --> 10:55.251
Mm, keep reading.

10:57.553 --> 10:59.488
"And I did what I did.

10:59.688 --> 11:01.424
I still relive the thuds

11:01.624 --> 11:04.994
that resulted from hitting
all of those people."

11:06.428 --> 11:09.581
"I still hear their screams.

11:09.781 --> 11:12.542
The guilt can be so much,

11:12.742 --> 11:15.074
which makes me think of you.

11:15.274 --> 11:17.406
You must be feeling guilt, too.

11:17.606 --> 11:21.277
After all, had you not left
your keys in the ignition...

11:21.477 --> 11:22.645
So many "ifs."

11:22.845 --> 11:24.113
If I had not been out walking,

11:24.313 --> 11:26.749
suffering from the insomnia that night."

11:26.949 --> 11:29.285
Had you not left the car unlocked,

11:29.485 --> 11:32.254
perhaps none of this
would have happened.

11:32.454 --> 11:35.424
Perhaps those innocent people
would still be alive.

11:35.624 --> 11:40.095
I want you to know,
I feel your anguish, Mrs. Trelawney.

11:40.295 --> 11:41.830
Compassionate little fuck, isn't he?

11:44.099 --> 11:46.635
"After all, we only have each other."

11:46.835 --> 11:50.072
Those innocent people
would still be alive,

11:50.272 --> 11:51.307
but for the two of us.

11:53.042 --> 11:56.445
Crazy as it may seem...

11:56.645 --> 11:59.782
you are the only person
keeping me alive.

12:01.650 --> 12:03.786
Really working her.

12:06.355 --> 12:08.324
"Because you're the only one
who can understand

12:08.524 --> 12:10.259
what it is like to be in hell.

12:11.460 --> 12:13.729
Sincerely, Mr. Mercedes."

12:15.364 --> 12:17.483
Probation? You got to be kidding me.

12:17.683 --> 12:19.602
We don't have a probation policy.

12:19.802 --> 12:22.037
No. He meant it like a warning,
like I could have got fired.

12:22.237 --> 12:24.373
Brady, we run this place.

12:24.573 --> 12:26.342
We make all the service calls.

12:26.542 --> 12:27.276
We work the floor.

12:27.476 --> 12:29.512
Robi doesn't know shit about computers.

12:29.712 --> 12:33.115
He just likes to boss us around
and hold dominion and shit.

12:33.315 --> 12:34.917
Mmph.

12:35.117 --> 12:36.419
What's going on?

12:36.619 --> 12:38.421
Um, just a migraine, stress thing.

12:38.621 --> 12:41.023
I'll be fine.
Yep, stress caused by Robi.

12:41.223 --> 12:42.291
We should report him to OSHA.

12:42.491 --> 12:43.692
Hey, I'll tell you what.

12:43.892 --> 12:45.894
He's always wanting us
to show initiative and shit.

12:46.094 --> 12:48.097
We should tell him
that while he was away at lunch,

12:48.297 --> 12:50.132
we started a human resources department

12:50.332 --> 12:51.967
and reported his fucking ass.

12:54.637 --> 12:56.605
What the fuck?
Who's working the register?

12:56.805 --> 12:58.507
What, you didn't see? I left a note...

12:58.707 --> 13:00.175
please help yourself.

13:01.977 --> 13:04.079
What? Paulie's out there. So is Tayles.

13:04.279 --> 13:05.915
No, no. They're retards. No.

13:06.115 --> 13:08.784
I don't want them working
the register unattended, so.

13:08.984 --> 13:10.586
Yeah. Well, I'm on my break.

13:10.786 --> 13:12.554
You're not.
I'll just be one minute.

13:12.754 --> 13:14.523
He was delayed because of a migraine

13:14.723 --> 13:15.458
brought on by your abuse,

13:15.658 --> 13:17.226
which is currently under investigation

13:17.426 --> 13:18.360
by our new HR wing.

13:18.560 --> 13:19.361
What?

13:19.561 --> 13:21.230
And what's with
the "Man From Glad" getup?

13:21.430 --> 13:23.866
What did I say about you selling
Popsicles during business hours?

13:24.066 --> 13:25.000
I was on break, so personal time.

13:25.200 --> 13:26.135
What are you, a drug dealer, Brady?

13:26.335 --> 13:27.536
Shut up.

13:34.109 --> 13:36.428
What did you say to me?

13:36.628 --> 13:38.947
I'm not a drug dealer.

13:39.147 --> 13:40.282
Uhhuh.

13:40.482 --> 13:42.584
Well, who you selling
ice cream to at lunchtime?

13:42.784 --> 13:44.319
I did a birthday party at a school.

13:44.519 --> 13:45.354
I don't sell drugs, you...

13:52.261 --> 13:54.496
I have had it with you two.

13:58.367 --> 14:01.070
Fuck.

14:01.270 --> 14:02.605
You really okay?

14:02.805 --> 14:05.174
Yeah. It's just a migraine, so.

14:07.242 --> 14:08.677
Go home.

14:08.877 --> 14:10.546
You're allowed to have a sick day.

14:10.746 --> 14:12.848
Just...go home.

14:13.048 --> 14:15.084
I'll deal with Robi.

14:15.284 --> 14:17.453
Thank you.

14:19.555 --> 14:23.926
With each one,
he keeps upping the emotional voltage.

14:24.126 --> 14:26.328
He keeps talking about his guilt,

14:26.528 --> 14:28.363
but he's really trying to...

14:28.563 --> 14:29.598
Uncork hers.

14:29.798 --> 14:31.233
Right.

14:31.433 --> 14:34.269
Well, I mean, the good thing about it is

14:34.469 --> 14:37.106
that this is what
we call "hard evidence."

14:37.306 --> 14:39.608
This is just the kind of thing
the police are looking for.

14:40.876 --> 14:43.245
I have a pretty good nose
for indifference,

14:43.445 --> 14:46.081
and I promise you,
the police don't give a shit.

14:46.281 --> 14:48.117
This is going to end up at the bottom

14:48.317 --> 14:49.218
of a... of a dusty file.

14:49.418 --> 14:51.620
If I don't go forward with this,

14:51.820 --> 14:53.922
I'm withholding evidence,

14:54.122 --> 14:56.025
which is a felony offense.

14:56.225 --> 14:59.161
I'd never get to vote
for President again.

15:00.562 --> 15:01.630
Okay.

15:01.830 --> 15:05.034
Well, I have done some research,

15:05.234 --> 15:10.072
and it seems that P.I.s make around...

15:10.272 --> 15:11.273
$5,000 a week.

15:11.473 --> 15:14.042
And I'm prepared to write
a personal check right now,

15:14.242 --> 15:15.578
make it completely official.

15:15.778 --> 15:18.747
Any communication
or conversations we have

15:18.947 --> 15:21.183
will be deemed work product.

15:21.383 --> 15:22.785
Mm.

15:22.985 --> 15:26.922
Okay.
Ms. Patterson, before I cash your check,

15:27.122 --> 15:31.059
I'm telling you I'm taking
this to the police.

15:31.259 --> 15:33.862
Then we'll see what happens next, okay?

15:34.062 --> 15:35.330
Okay.

15:53.382 --> 15:55.884
Well, I guess news travels fast.
Who told you?

15:56.084 --> 15:57.686
Told me what? I haven't heard shit.

15:57.886 --> 15:59.488
You serious?

16:00.556 --> 16:01.824
Bill, we caught him.

16:04.126 --> 16:05.327
Caught who?

16:05.527 --> 16:07.262
Oh, my God. You really didn't hear.

16:07.462 --> 16:08.931
Donnie Davis.

16:09.131 --> 16:11.433
And get this...
that asshole didn't just kill his wife.

16:11.633 --> 16:13.936
Turns out he's Turnpike Joe.
He killed all those hookers.

16:14.136 --> 16:15.904
We just hit the fucking lottery here.

16:16.104 --> 16:18.473
Oh, that's... that's fantastic.

16:18.673 --> 16:20.843
Jesus, try not to get too excited.

16:21.043 --> 16:23.045
No, no, no. TThat's...
That's great, really.

16:25.113 --> 16:27.316
Can I talk to you for a second?

16:27.516 --> 16:30.619
Yeah. Come on.

16:30.819 --> 16:32.588
So these are the ones he sent to me.

16:32.788 --> 16:34.790
These others are what
led her to suicide.

16:34.990 --> 16:37.259
There's things in there
only the killer could know.

16:37.459 --> 16:39.094
This is not hoax shit.

16:39.294 --> 16:40.462
Okay. Okay.

16:40.662 --> 16:44.533
Bill, great, we'll take it from here.

16:44.733 --> 16:45.534
Private conversation.

16:45.734 --> 16:47.936
Izzy's working the case with me.
It's all right.

16:48.136 --> 16:49.938
Oh, really?
Hi, Bill.

16:50.138 --> 16:52.941
Bill has received some letters
he believes might be pertinent

16:53.141 --> 16:56.245
to the, uh... Mercedes investigation.

16:56.445 --> 16:58.047
Aha.

16:58.247 --> 17:00.049
"Aha"? That's it?

17:00.249 --> 17:02.384
No curiosity as to
what the letters contain?

17:02.584 --> 17:03.185
These are from him.

17:03.385 --> 17:04.953
Bill, how would you know?

17:05.153 --> 17:06.722
And please don't tell me your gut.

17:06.922 --> 17:10.525
Huh? I mean,
this "I was sexually abused and bullied"

17:10.724 --> 17:12.894
boilerplate,
that's particularly him, is it?

17:13.094 --> 17:15.064
And what about the integrity
of this evidence?

17:15.263 --> 17:17.598
How many people have
touched these letters before me?

17:17.799 --> 17:19.351
What's going on here? I'm on your team.

17:19.550 --> 17:21.103
No, Bill. No. You're off the team.

17:21.303 --> 17:22.104
You're retired.

17:24.473 --> 17:26.141
Now, I'm grateful you brought these in.

17:26.340 --> 17:27.959
They'll be reviewed by us and the shrink

17:28.159 --> 17:29.778
and any others who can lend
an expert hand.

17:29.978 --> 17:31.480
Pete, '93 or '94?
'94.

17:31.680 --> 17:32.948
See? There's '94.

17:33.148 --> 17:35.150
Now, I'll...
I'll pull the prints off them.

17:35.350 --> 17:37.085
And once we've ruled out yours and mine

17:37.285 --> 17:38.987
and the sister's and Olivia Trelawney's

17:39.187 --> 17:40.689
and her housekeeper's and the mother's

17:40.889 --> 17:43.025
and any neighbors
they thought to share them with,

17:43.225 --> 17:45.694
I'll see if his are on there, too.
Hmm? When?

17:45.894 --> 17:47.996
When we finish taking
the statement of Donnie Davis.

17:48.196 --> 17:50.299
And then formally charge him
and then take his statement

17:50.499 --> 17:51.200
on the turnpike killings

17:51.400 --> 17:53.035
and then write up all our reports

17:53.235 --> 17:54.770
and then maybe, oh, maybe,

17:54.970 --> 17:56.605
squeeze in, oh, 4 hours of sleep.

17:56.805 --> 17:58.240
Then maybe we reach out to the shrink

17:58.440 --> 18:00.109
who might just point out
how these letters

18:00.309 --> 18:02.411
don't seem all that different
from the 700 others

18:02.611 --> 18:03.879
we received from all over the country

18:04.079 --> 18:06.415
and two from Gstaad claiming
to be the Mercedes Killer.

18:06.615 --> 18:08.283
Is that good enough for you, Bill?

18:08.483 --> 18:10.886
Who the fuck are you?

18:11.086 --> 18:12.354
Don't talk to me that way.

18:12.554 --> 18:14.189
