36:52.002 --> 36:52.903
Yeah.

36:53.103 --> 36:55.706
Ollie took such good care of her.

36:55.906 --> 36:57.858
You can really see the decline since...
Yeah.

36:58.058 --> 37:00.010
Do you think maybe
we could wait in the hall?

37:04.481 --> 37:07.384
What's the matter?

37:07.584 --> 37:09.019
Nothing.

37:17.027 --> 37:18.595
I got some condition.

37:18.795 --> 37:20.163
It's not posttraumatic.

37:20.363 --> 37:24.034
It's...seein'
dead people puts me on a little tilt.

37:24.234 --> 37:26.436
Thanks.

37:26.636 --> 37:27.671
I realize your mother isn't dead,

37:27.871 --> 37:29.239
but she was looking
the part pretty good,

37:32.442 --> 37:34.778
One of the other consequences
of that night.

37:34.978 --> 37:37.180
There was so much death. It was carnage.

37:37.380 --> 37:40.050
I can't imagine.

37:46.857 --> 37:48.725
Did you sister talk much of it?

37:48.925 --> 37:51.411
The guilt?

37:51.611 --> 37:53.897
Not to me.

37:54.097 --> 37:58.702
Truth be told,
I don't know that she felt much guilt.

37:58.902 --> 38:03.240
I think she felt oppressed by the end.

38:03.440 --> 38:04.908
Blamed.

38:05.108 --> 38:08.745
I don't know that she
really felt guilty.

38:08.945 --> 38:10.781
A man stole her car. Yeah.

38:10.981 --> 38:13.884
Yeah, it's just if she hadn't
left the keys in the ignition...

38:14.084 --> 38:15.018
She didn't.

38:15.218 --> 38:16.686
Hmm?

38:18.488 --> 38:19.906
He said it in the letters.

38:20.106 --> 38:21.325
I don't care what he said.

38:21.525 --> 38:24.327
He was just fucking with her mind.

38:24.527 --> 38:27.064
My sister was many things,

38:27.264 --> 38:29.700
honest and fastidious being two.

38:29.900 --> 38:34.137
It's completely unlike her
to leave her keys in her car.

38:34.337 --> 38:37.123
And if she said she didn't, she didn't.

38:37.323 --> 38:40.110
You're really convinced about that?

38:40.310 --> 38:41.311
A hundred percent.

38:41.511 --> 38:44.381
It's just...

38:46.583 --> 38:49.085
the car door wasn't jimmied
or hotwired or anything.

38:49.285 --> 38:50.187
She didn't leave her keys
in the ignition.

38:55.192 --> 38:56.326
Are we having a fight?

38:59.696 --> 39:02.465
I didn't really like
your sister very much.

39:02.665 --> 39:04.884
I found her a bit cold.

39:05.084 --> 39:07.304
There's no need to explain.

39:07.504 --> 39:10.607
You didn't like her.

39:10.807 --> 39:12.676
Guess we are having a fight.

39:16.479 --> 39:19.416
I didn't much like her, either.

39:19.616 --> 39:21.418
I loved her, quite dearly.

39:21.618 --> 39:25.755
Liking her proved much more difficult.

39:41.104 --> 39:42.806
Hey, boss.

39:43.006 --> 39:44.708
How you doing today?

39:46.910 --> 39:48.378
Told you I hate dogs.
Especially this one.

39:50.313 --> 39:52.649
So, listen, I did some digging

39:52.849 --> 39:54.985
into Under Debbie's Blue Umbrella.

39:55.185 --> 39:59.155
Definitely not a straw man,
more like a... a Yeti.

39:59.355 --> 40:00.323
A what?

40:00.523 --> 40:01.291
A Yeti?

40:01.491 --> 40:03.060
Abominable Snowman.

40:03.260 --> 40:05.061
Okay, look, whatever.
Call it what you will.

40:05.261 --> 40:06.463
What I'm saying is, this umbrella thing

40:06.663 --> 40:07.531
is a monster, man.

40:07.731 --> 40:08.799
It's locked up like Fort Knox.

40:08.999 --> 40:10.367
I've been trying to get in, but I can't.

40:10.567 --> 40:11.902
Shit. Yeah.

40:12.102 --> 40:14.571
Listen, Jerome. The...

40:14.771 --> 40:17.474
Your old man was by to see me.

40:17.674 --> 40:18.508
What? Yeah.

40:18.708 --> 40:19.810
He's concerned... rightly so...

40:20.010 --> 40:21.745
that I've maybe got you
mixed up in something dangerous.

40:21.945 --> 40:23.346
Oh.

40:23.546 --> 40:24.897
Well, do you?

40:25.097 --> 40:26.249
Could be.

40:26.449 --> 40:29.286
Possibly about to become more so.

40:29.486 --> 40:31.221
Best to stay away for the time being,
all right?

40:31.421 --> 40:33.757
Um...oh.

40:33.957 --> 40:35.659
Well, who's gonna mow your lawn, then?

40:35.859 --> 40:38.595
Oh. Was thinking of getting
it paved over anyway.

40:38.795 --> 40:41.531
Well, unless you're planning
on not communicating

40:41.731 --> 40:43.216
with whoever this mystery person is...

40:43.416 --> 40:44.901
I mean, you need I.T. help, Mr. Hodges.

40:45.101 --> 40:46.336
Come on.

40:46.536 --> 40:48.038
Well, I won't be getting it from you.

40:48.238 --> 40:50.240
I mean it. What?!

40:50.440 --> 40:52.242
Oh, come on. Not even a hug?

40:52.442 --> 40:54.577
One hug?

40:58.415 --> 41:00.383
Okay. I'll settle for a Chipwich.

41:00.583 --> 41:01.518
Come on, one Chipwich.

41:04.454 --> 41:06.856
Ha. Thank you.

41:07.056 --> 41:09.008
Yo.

41:09.208 --> 41:13.130
Hey!

41:13.330 --> 41:15.598
What the fuck?

41:20.637 --> 41:22.205
Probably some drug dealer,

41:22.405 --> 41:23.773
knows you're an excop.

41:23.973 --> 41:27.243
But, hey,
sugar's probably worse than drugs.

41:27.443 --> 41:28.211
I'll catch you, Mr. Hodges.

41:59.709 --> 42:01.644
Nothing?

42:01.844 --> 42:03.963
No, not a chirp.

42:04.163 --> 42:06.082
I'm surprised.

42:06.282 --> 42:11.154
Maybe he's plotting a...
a proper response, or...

42:11.354 --> 42:13.656
Or? Or what?

42:13.856 --> 42:15.758
Or it's not him.

42:15.958 --> 42:17.861
And the game's over.

42:18.061 --> 42:19.596
No. It's him.

42:23.299 --> 42:25.402
It has to be him.

42:25.602 --> 42:28.171
We're both a bit desperate for that,
aren't we?

42:28.371 --> 42:31.141
Oh, yes, you are

42:31.341 --> 42:34.677
What are we up to here? You and me?

42:34.877 --> 42:38.214
Something happened, something big

42:38.414 --> 42:40.683
Happened to me that day

42:40.883 --> 42:42.953
Sorry? What do you mean?

42:43.153 --> 42:46.673
It's not like we're
on a dogood mission.

42:46.873 --> 42:50.193
It's more like we're settling a score.

42:50.393 --> 42:52.462
Take a killer off the street,
it does a lot of good.

42:52.662 --> 42:54.664
That's not why we're doing it.

42:54.864 --> 42:55.765
We're not trying to help.

42:55.965 --> 43:00.303
It's like we both
have vengeance on the brain.

43:00.503 --> 43:01.604
Nothing wrong with a little vengeance.

43:01.804 --> 43:03.873
Oh, yes, you are

43:04.073 --> 43:05.642
Ain't just love makes
the world go round.

43:08.478 --> 43:10.980
You love anybody, Bill?

43:15.084 --> 43:16.719
Feels like we're changing the subject.

43:20.090 --> 43:22.092
Tell me about your family.

43:22.292 --> 43:24.294
Why did you leave Ireland?

43:25.328 --> 43:28.531
'Cause I wanted to.

43:28.731 --> 43:30.867
I mean, II don't have a family.

43:31.067 --> 43:32.035
What about your ex-wife?

43:32.235 --> 43:33.253
What happened there?

43:33.453 --> 43:34.471
Creative differences.

43:38.608 --> 43:40.677
And your daughter?

43:43.546 --> 43:47.617
Something sad, something blue

43:47.817 --> 43:51.888
Something lost, something I found

43:52.088 --> 43:54.891
Since my woman put me down

43:55.091 --> 43:55.992
Do you know...

43:56.192 --> 43:59.128
do you think it would be possible

43:59.328 --> 44:02.065
your mother might rebound tomorrow?

44:02.265 --> 44:05.235
I really want to know
what Olivia told her, you know?

44:05.435 --> 44:07.904
Well...

44:08.104 --> 44:11.541
overdue for a good day.

44:11.741 --> 44:12.825
We can go back.

44:13.025 --> 44:14.110
Good, good.

44:27.357 --> 44:29.125
When was the last time you danced?

44:29.325 --> 44:32.395
I danced?

44:32.595 --> 44:35.064
Seven... The '70s.

44:38.568 --> 44:41.104
I think you're long overdue.

44:41.871 --> 44:44.441
Come on.

44:44.641 --> 44:47.193
Let's have a dance. Come on.

44:47.393 --> 44:49.946
you must face them alone

44:50.146 --> 44:51.814
Please.

44:54.217 --> 44:58.071
Please remember

44:58.271 --> 45:01.925
I still want you

45:02.125 --> 45:08.064
And in case you wonder why

45:08.264 --> 45:12.369
Well, just wake up

45:12.569 --> 45:18.575
Kiss the good life goodbye

45:18.775 --> 45:20.777
Brady?

45:20.977 --> 45:22.145
Honey?

45:31.287 --> 45:33.122
It's a bad one, isn't it?

45:33.322 --> 45:35.591
Like a vise.

45:35.791 --> 45:37.861
Oh, baby.

45:38.061 --> 45:40.263
Come here. Come to Mama, honey boy.

45:40.463 --> 45:41.131
Come here.

45:41.331 --> 45:45.068
Baby. Come here.

45:45.268 --> 45:47.103
Come on.

45:50.373 --> 45:55.612
<i>Oh, the good life</i>

45:55.812 --> 45:58.748
<i>Full of fun, seems to be</i>

45:58.948 --> 46:01.651
<i>The ideal</i>

46:01.851 --> 46:04.354
<i>Ahh, ahh, ahh</i>

46:04.554 --> 46:09.159
<i>Yes, the good life</i>

46:09.359 --> 46:14.897
<i>Lets you hide all the sadness you feel</i>

46:18.968 --> 46:23.039
<i>Mama's gonna make it better.</i>

46:23.239 --> 46:27.310
<i>You won't really fall in love</i>

46:27.510 --> 46:32.782
<i>For you can't the chance</i>

46:32.982 --> 46:37.153
<i>So be honest</i>

46:37.353 --> 46:41.324
<i>With yourself</i>

46:41.524 --> 46:47.664
<i>Don't try to fake romance</i>

46:47.864 --> 46:52.368
<i>It's the good life</i>

46:52.568 --> 46:58.408
<i>To be free and explore the unknown</i>

47:03.179 --> 47:06.549
<i>Like the heartaches</i>

47:06.749 --> 47:13.423
<i>When you learn you must face them alone</i>

47:17.627 --> 47:21.297
<i>Please remember</i>

47:21.497 --> 47:24.968
<i>I still want you</i>

47:25.168 --> 47:31.174
<i>And in case you wonder why</i>

47:31.374 --> 47:35.411
<i>Well, just wake up</i>

47:35.611 --> 47:43.319
<i>Kiss the good life goodbye</i>

48:29.132 --> 48:32.885
<i>Please remember</i>

48:33.085 --> 48:36.639
<i>I still want you</i>

48:36.839 --> 48:42.845
<i>And in case you wonder why</i>

48:43.045 --> 48:47.166
<i>Well, just wake up</i>

48:47.366 --> 48:51.487
<i>Kiss the good life</i>

